The Office of Management and Budget (OMB) Director Mick Mulvaney released a statement following President Trump's signing of the Energy and Water, Legislative Branch, and Military Construction and Veterans Affairs Appropriations Act, 2019. The statement highlights the President's commitment to prioritize funding for national defense and those who serve to protect the country. The legislation includes investments in the military, veterans, and infrastructure, showing support for veterans, men and women in uniform, and their families. The Administration worked with Congress to provide historic funding for the Department of Veterans Affairs, modernize the VA health record system, provide new homes for military families, and invest in a national nuclear security strategy. The statement emphasizes that President Trump is keeping his promises to prioritize the nation's heroes while protecting American taxpayers.